<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-09T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-09T12:00:00-05:00" n="29" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.5151/201: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sevier</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-09T13:00:00-04:00">July 9, 1934—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>51. Your telegram No. 50, June 2, 3 p.m. In view of the visit of Messrs.
                            Williams and Heath of which you were apprised in telegraphic instruction
                            No. 50, July 3, 7 p.m.,<note n="17" xml:id="d29fn17">Not printed; see
                                instruction No. 52, July 5, 1934, to the Ambassador in Chile, <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> you may hold negotiations in
                            abeyance pending an opportunity to discuss the matter with Mr. Williams.
                            Consult the Department before taking further action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>